        "source_completion_round": 15,
        "body": "Make pid-record liveness actually work on non-Linux Unix platforms by honoring the fallback start marker, or explicitly gate the feature to Linux. `src/adapters/fs.rs:337-357` only treats `proc_start_ticks` as authoritative and returns `false` whenever ticks are absent, while non-Linux builds only populate `proc_start_marker` (`src/adapters/fs.rs:701-704`). Because `src/cli/run.rs:1529-1568` falls back to legacy lease handling when the pid record is not authoritative, macOS/BSD runs cannot be identified or recovered immediately from `run.pid` and remain blocked until the writer lease expires.",
